This paper proposes methods to classify Thin-cap fibroatheroma (TCFA) using various machine learning classifiers and suggests a pixel range based feature extraction method. The use of machine learning classifiers and feature extraction methods suggests that this paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of neural networks (FNN and CNN) suggests that this paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of K-Nearest Neighbor (KNN) and Random Forest (RF) classifiers suggests that this paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of ROC curve analysis suggests that this paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
